{
  "texts": [
    "Specifically, the co-share network is obtained by connecting accounts if they share links to the same sources.",
    "It is thus a weighted, undirected graph where the nodes are accounts having at least one shared source in common with another account.",
    "Each account is represented as a vector of shared domains.",
    "To mitigate the effect of popular sources on the similarity among accounts, we use Term Frequency -Inverse Document Frequency (TF-IDF) vector representations [54] where each dimension is a news source.",
    "Edges correspond to co-share interactions and are weighted by the cosine similarity between the TF-IDF vectors of the two connected accounts."
  ]
}